<text evidence="2">Expression is strongly activated (7-fold at 16 degrees Celsius compared to 37 degrees) at low temperature.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="disruption phenotype">
<text evidence="2 3">3- to 20-fold derepression of several genes coding for small proteins including the ycgZ-ymgA-ariR-ymgC operon. While the BluR/F system is induced at low temperatures under blue light irradiation, it is not essential for growth under these conditions. When both lon and bluR are disrupted, levels of OmpF decrease, leading to lower drug susceptibility, with a greater effect at 26 degrees than at 37 degrees Celsius. The mechanism is not yet understood.</text>
</comment>
